For the hard of hearing, the fast talking and low loaning may be difficult, so here's a transcript:
Nick: Hey - so what's the plan?
Simon: Right. Call Mum, make sure she's OK. If Phillip has been infected, follow the NHS guidelines to the letter.
Nick: Don't you want to kill him?
Simon: Well of course I want to kill him, I just... can't right now.
Nick: Awwww.
Simon: Don't go to Liz's.
Nick: But what if I'm horny?
Simon: Well she's my girlfriend!
Nick: Alright! Grey...
Simon: What do you mean, alright grey? Ah! Yep. I see what you're doing. I know it's 2020, but the original joke wasn't intended as homophobic. It was more a comment on the absurdity of straight male appropriation of homophobic signifiers in order to denote their aversion to emotional candidness.
Nick: *Exasperated sigh, waffling hand gesture*
Simon: Do NOT go to the Winchester. The pub is out.
Nick: Even if it's shut?
Simon: Especially if it's closed. Remember what happened he last time?
Nick: Yeah! *makes zombie noises whilst fondling controller*
Simon: Yep.
Nick: *makes zombie noises whilst fondling controller*
Simon: Yep.
Nick: *makes zombie noises whilst fondling controller*
Simon: Yep.
Nick: *tails off on zombie noises*
Simon: If you can, stay at home. Have a cup of tea. And wait for all this to blow over. Above all, don't be a twat about things. We're all in this together. Don't be selfish. Look after each other. Give someone a call if you think they might be lonely. OK? How are you doing?
Nick: *big breath* I'm running out of toilet paper. Have you got any?
Simon: Ah. Yes, Sorry mate, I'm down to my last, uh, sheet. Uh. You take care buddy. Bye! Bye-bye! *hangs up" *sits and drinks his tea* *winks*
